#	Description: The data are oxygen isotopic measurements from modern and fossil corals  collected from Palmyra Island (6???N, 162???W). The sequences range in age from 930A.D.  to the 20th century, are 30 to 150 years long, and are presented at  monthly resolution. The sample names refer to collection sites on  Palmyra Island (see Figure 1 of Nature paper). See Supplementary Info.  associated with the Nature article for more detailed geochemical and  chronological information.
